Subject: New release of Caml Light for Windows
Sender: weis
Status: O


A new release of Caml Light 0.71 for Windows is now available 
on ftp.inria.fr, directory lang/caml-light, file cl71win2.zip.

This release fixes all known bugs in the graphical interface, in 
particular in the graphics primitives. 

The command-line compilers are no longer limited to Windows 95 
or NT. They now work under  Windows 3.1, MS-DOS or any 
DPMI-compliant operating system. 

Finally, the libnum library for arbitrary-precision rational 
arithmetic is now available both at toplevel and in separately 
compiled programs.

Please report bugs to caml-light@pauillac.inria.fr

Jean-Marie Geffroy
Xavier Leroy

http://pauillac.inria.fr/caml





